I started today by learning if, else if and else in more detail and I also learnt the Ternary Operator. I had a go at making a simple system which checks if you are an adult or a minor.

<script>
let age = 21;
let text = (age < 18) ?  "Minor" : "Adult";

document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML = text;
</script>

I then learnt about Switch Statements and all the important keywords that come with it like break, default, and case! I then made a simple script which showed the user what day it currently was using the Date().getDay() method, aswell as a switch statement.

let day;
let date = new Date().getDay();
 
<script>
switch (date) {
  case 0:
    day = "Sunday";
    break;
  case 1:
    day = "Monday";
    break;
</script>
